  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 112:9",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 112:9",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He hath dispersed — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His goods, freely and liberally. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He hath given to the poor — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To such as he knew to be really in want, and especially to the poor members of Christ. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His righteousness — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His liberality, or the reward of it; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "endureth for ever ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, either, 1st, His charity is not a transient or occasional act; it is his constant course, of which he is not weary, but perseveres in it to the end of his life. Or, 2d, What he gives is not lost, as covetous or ungodly men judge of what is given to the poor, but, indeed, is the only part of his estate which will abide with him unto all eternity. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His horn shall be exalted, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Though he may now be reproached by the wicked, yet his innocence shall be cleared, and his name and honour gloriously exalted, especially when Jesus shall say to him and others of his saints, at the great day, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I was hungry, and ye gave me meat, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. “Then, when the thrones of the mighty shall be cast down. and the sceptres of tyrants broken in pieces, shall he lift up his head and be exalted, to partake of the glory of his Redeemer, the author of his faith, and the pattern of his charity, who gave himself for us, and is now seated at the right hand of the majesty in the heavens.” — Horne.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
